      "name": "Our Story",
      "settings": {
        "background_color": "#f3f1e3",
        "heading": "The color",
        "text": "<p>White diamonds naturally vary in colour, ranging from the extremely rare, colourless stones to warm white diamonds with a soft yellow tint. The subtle differences in hue are caused by trace amounts of nitrogen present during the diamond’s formation deep within the earth.<br/><br/>To classify these variations, the industry uses a colour grading scale of 23 shades, assigning each diamond a letter from D (colourless) to Z (light yellow). Among them, D-colour diamonds are the most coveted for their exceptional purity and rarity.<br/><br/></p>",
        "button_label": "Learn more",
